sentences: Karina Pasian (born July 18, 1991) is an American singer, songwriter and pianist.
In 2003, Pasian met Quincy Jones, who invited her and her family to his home in Bel Air, California.
She also performed at Quincy Jones' We Are The Future concert in Rome.
On June 22, 2007, Pasian performed at the White House for President George W. Bush, in celebration of Black Music Month, making her the first person of Dominican descent to perform there.

She chose Def Jam in 2006.
Her first album First Love was released on August 19, 2008.
Later that year, the album received a nomination for a Grammy Award in the category of "Best Contemporary R&B."
